{
  "text": "The rate of wound closure is estimated by considering the extent of the non-epithelialized region in each case (see the electronic supplementary material for further details). Figure 6 shows the wound takes much longer to heal than in the normal case, which is in agreement with the conclusions of Oberringer et al. [CITATION_1] . Additionally, as seen in figure 5 , our model predicts that collagen is produced at a slower rate than in the normal case.",
